RACE.FOOTNOTES: IN HONOR OF AUTISM raced close to the decent early pace while outside of runners, advanced two wide on the turn, shifted to the three path into the stretch, battled with STRENGTH OF AUTISM to the furlong marker, drew to even terms outside of STRENGTH OF AUTISM heading to the sixteenth-marker, dueled into deep stretch with STRENGTH OF AUTISM, took a narrow lead in the final strides and lasted at the finish to prevail. RACE.FOOTNOTES: BROKEN FINGER never far back, settled along the inside into the first turn, was well positioned while saving ground through the backstretch run, was roused approaching the quarter marker, angled four wide into the stretch and loomed nearing the furlong grounds, took command inside of the furlong marker and drew away under moderate urging in deep stretch. GORDY'S BOY was forwardly placed into the first turn, stalked the decent pace into the backstretch run and steadily advanced on N. K. ROCKET MAN heading into the far turn, overtook that rival leaving the quarter marker and vied with EMERALD MAGIC into the stretch, could not keep pace with BROKEN FINGER inside of the furlong marker, was outfinished in deep stretch and held well in the end for second. EMERALD MAGIC tracked the early pace three wide into the first turn, improved position along the backstretch run and was well placed heading to the half-mile marker, continued to gain three wide approaching the quarter marker, vied for the lead into the stretch and battled with GORDY'S BOY to mid-stretch, could not muster the needed response in the final furlong, was outkicked and held clearly for third. MY SUNSHINE settled inside of rivals to begin, maintained a two wide path through the backstretch run tracking solid fractions, mounted a five wide bid into the stretch and improved position heading to the furlong marker, could not sustain that run into deep stretch and flattened out. N. K. ROCKET MAN was a step slow to begin, was hustled in the early stages and assumed command into the first turn, dictated terms off of the rail into the backstretch run, set solid fractions controlling the pace to the half-mile pole, came under pressure along the far turn, was overtaken leaving the quarter marker and tired in the stretch drive. WALKING BOSS settled outside of rivals into the turn, maintained a four wide path through the backstretch run, was coaxed along three wide into the far turn and did not threaten in the stretch.

ENTRY.COMMENT: off step slow,hustled,set solid pace,overtaken 3/16,tired stretch

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MORNING ADDICTION was away in good order and was prominent early, pressed the solid early pace outside of BLUEBERRY MUFFIN, dueled for the lead into the turn with that rival, took a narrow advantage two wide and between runners at the quarter marker, shook free into the stretch, was kept to moderate urging into the final furlong, drew off into deep stretch and was hand ridden to the finish to prevail as much the best. BIG MAMA THORNTON broke a step slowly away from the gate, rushed up and raced close to the quick early pace outside of the leading pair, pressed three wide at the quarter marker, lost ground into the stretch, was not able to impact the runaway winner in the late stages but ran on in deep stretch and was up in the final strides to secure the place. PERFECTLY JULIE was pinched back at the start and was away a bit slowly, chased the fast early pace outside of an inner rival, gave chase three wide to the quarter marker, came four wide into the stretch, lacked the needed response in the final furlong and just missed for the place, while getting up in time for the show in a blanket finish for the minor awards. BLUEBERRY MUFFIN broke alertly and contested the fast early pace with MORNING ADDICTION, dueled inside of that rival into the turn, lost the lead to MORNING ADDICTION approaching the top of the lane, chased into the stretch, tired in the late stages and was outfinished for the minor awards. AIR FORCE WOMAN chased the quick early pace from a two wide path, was coaxed along four wide into the stretch, lost ground heading to the furlong marker and weakened in the final stages. O'NEILL'S LEGACY lacked early speed, raced three wide to the quarter marker, trailed into the stretch and did not threaten.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MARY MARGARET broke out at the start and was away a step slowly, recovered and tracked the decent pace from a two wide path and between runners, waited for racing room approaching the quarter marker, swung four wide into the stretch, angled six wide approaching the furlong marker, responded to urging and vied for the lead heading to the sixteenth-marker, took a narrow lead into deep stretch and held the runner-up at bay in the final stages to prevail. SHEMAKESCENTS was sent leaving an alert beginning and set pressured early fractions, shook free into the turn and set the pace from off the rail heading to the quarter marker, showed the way into upper stretch and drifted to the three path into the drive, was confronted by MARY MARGARET inside of the furlong pole, was overtaken in deep stretch and was outfinished in the final stages, while holding safely for second. KITTEN'S KID stalked the decent early pace from the inside, remained close to the pace while chasing along the turn, came two wide into the stretch, raced within aim into the drive and chased to the furlong marker, lacked the needed response in deep stretch, was outkicked and just held for third at the wire. SMOOVE AS SILK tracked the early pace from the inside, saved ground into the turn, waited a bit for racing room nearing the top of the stretch, found room along the inside into the drive and advanced heading to the furlong marker, could not sustain that run into deep stretch, flattened out and just missed for third at the finish. DRAW NEAR chased the decent early pace while outside of rivals, came three wide to the quarter marker and swung five wide for the stretch drive, was outrun to mid-stretch and tired in the late going. SEASON TO REMEMBER was sent away from the start, pressed the decent early pace outside of SHEMAKESCENTS, maintained a three wide path to the quarter marker while pressing the pace, came four wide into the stretch, lost position into upper stretch and gave way in the final furlong.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DR LOW KEY was forwardly placed away from the start and tracked the solid early pace, inched closer two wide along the turn and was roused three wide into the stretch, took command into upper stretch and was set down at the furlong marker, was kept to task into deep stretch, held foes at bay in the final sixteenth and held safely in a drive at the finish to prevail. CHAMPAGNE PEGASUS stalked the solid early pace from the inside, gained ground heading to the quarter marker, maintained an inside path into upper stretch and continued to improve position heading to the furlong grounds, was gaining in deep stretch but could not reel in the winner in the final stages and just held for second at the finish. BIG DON'S SMILING took back and rated off of the solid early pace, gained ground from a two wide path on the turn, tipped three wide for the drive, closed well in the late stages, just missed for second and held safely in the end for third. THE SANDY SURPRISE was squeezed by neighboring rivals leaving the start and was off slowly, chased from the rear early on, gained ground two wide along the turn, came three wide into the stretch and offered a mild rally in the final furlong. DAD BOD was hustled away from the start and assumed command in the early stages, sped to the early lead and set the fast pace into the turn, dictated terms along the bend while carving decent fractions, drifted to the two path into upper stretch, was overtaken by DR LOW KEY heading to the furlong marker, remained in contention into deep stretch and gave way in the final sixteenth. HUMBLEBUMBLEFUMBLE bobbled at the start and was off slowly, chased from the rear in the early stages, saved ground into the turn, lacked a response in the stretch and did not threaten. RIGHT TURN chased the solid early pace outside of rivals, ran in pursuit three wide along the turn, dropped back approaching the top of the lane and tired.

WELLSWORT (IRE) tracked the moderate early pace outside of a rival, gained ground along the backstretch run, continued that gain three wide into the far turn, vied for the lead into upper stretch, vied between rivals at the furlong grounds, could not keep pace with SPEED GRAZY into deep stretch, was outkicked and held safely for second at the finish. CHIEF WILD EAGLE was prominent away from the gate, was asked to rate into the first turn and was a bit keen stalking the pace in the early stages, settled into the backstretch run and stalked the moderate pace to the half-mile marker, improved position heading into the far turn, chased two wide into upper stretch, could not match strides at the furlong marker and weakened in deep stretch. RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 7 1M Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $2,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MARKSMAN ON TARGET broke well and was up with the early leaders through the first turn racing two deep, was content to stalk FANTASTIC DREAM to the far turn then was set loose passing the seven-sixteenths marker, took over the lead along with ALGERIA (IRE) to the inside, was going better than that foe at the top of the stretch, pulled ahead and held off all challengers. DUPLICATION was up with the leaders going into the first turn fanned four wide, dropped back and raced in mid-pack, still wide down the backstretch, started to rally on the far turn, with ITS THIEVERY also making a move to the inside, loomed into contention at the top of the stretch, kept to task to the wire but was unable to catch the winner. FANTASTIC DREAM broke alertly and showed good speed from the start, was first into the turn with a trio fanned out across the track, emerged from that turn with the lead, stayed on the rail then checked near the three-eighths pole when ALGERIA (IRE) took the rail, lost momentum then came under pressure shortly thereafter and found new life at the quarter pole, had a wall of horses in front turning into the stretch, changed course to the six or seven path on the far outside then found a hole in mid-stretch and surged inside to gain third. BEROLIJEAN (FR) bobbled after the break and was a little slow to get going then raced well behind the field while saving ground, was asked to pick it up with a half-mile to run, made some slow but steady forward progress through the far turn, swung six wide into the stretch, kept grinding away to the wire but came up just short of a minor award. ITS THIEVERY raced mid-pack stalking the leaders three to four deep, launched a bid in tandem with DUPLICATION from about the seven-sixteenths pole, got a good run into the stretch in the two path and ran on well to the wire but but was outkicked in the late stages. ALGERIA (IRE) raced close up stalking FANTASTIC DREAM to the far turn, bid from the seven-sixteenths alongside MARKSMAN ON TARGET, could not keep up with that foe after passing the quarter pole then weakened and was outfinished down the stretch. TAKE THE TWO TEN broke a beat slow and lacked early speed from the break, lagged behind the field throughout, raced on the wrong lead through much of the stretch and was never a threat.
